<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-05-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-05-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="288" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d288">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Bailey</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">San
                                        José</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-05-09"><hi rend="italic">May 9,
                                1906</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Bailey reports that the Nicaraguan minister for foreign affairs has
                            been assassinated.)</p>
